Key Features:
1. WAS 8.5.5.25 Compatibility
Uses Jython 2.1 syntax (except Exception, e:)
Compatible with WAS 8.5.5 AdminConfig/AdminControl APIs
No modern Python features that would break in Jython 2.1
2. Properties File Configuration
Reads hostname mappings from hostname_mapping.properties
Supports primary and alternative hostnames
Easy to configure without modifying script
3. Comprehensive Hostname Updates
Updates serverName property
Updates databaseName property
Updates URL property
Updates alternative hostnames (clientRerouteAlternateServerName, alternateServers, failoverServers)
4. Enhanced Validation
Tests datasource connections AFTER changes are saved and synced
Handles "Undefined variable WAS_INSTALL_ROOT" errors gracefully
Skips problematic datasources and continues testing
Returns detailed status: passed, failed, skipped_server_not_running, skipped_was_install_root
5. Detailed Summary Report
Shows:

Hostname changes (old → new)
All datasources updated with their test status
Connection test results breakdown
Overall status with actionable recommendations
Files Created:
update_datasource_hostnames.py - Main script
hostname_mapping.properties - Configuration file (template)
Usage:
# 1. Edit hostname_mapping.properties with your values
# 2. Run the script
wsadmin.sh -lang jython -f update_datasource_hostnames.py

# Or specify custom properties file
wsadmin.sh -lang jython -f update_datasource_hostnames.py /path/to/custom.properties

